{"kind":"article","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC23","title":"Meet Assistive Access"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc23-10032-meet-assistive-access"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10032","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (8 min)","type":"reference"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10032-Meet-Assistive-Access"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Chapters","level":2,"text":"Chapters"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10032"},{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10032?time=81"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10032?time=175","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10032?time=280","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc23\/10032?time=323","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Overview","level":1,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"text":"Setup","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Setup"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Customizable interface","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Easy-to-add preferred apps","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"Assistive Access can be turned on in the Settings app. It helps parents or guardians to configure the device to the person that is going to use it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Lock Screen","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Lock-Screen"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Customizable wallpapers","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Quick look at notifications"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once entering into Assistive Access, the system displays a new lock screen with the capability to change its wallpaper in settings and an interface to inform people of notifications.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC23-10032-lockScreen"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Home screen","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Home-screen"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Large Icons"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Large text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Apps","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Apps"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Calls","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Messages"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Music","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Camera","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Photos","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Home screen is now displaying larger app icons and larger text, and apps adopting it, displays larger content."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC23-10032-homeScreen","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC23-10032-homeScreen2"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Principles of Assistive Access","level":1,"type":"heading","anchor":"Principles-of-Assistive-Access"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Streamlined task completion"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Error prevention and recovery","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Consistency","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Streamlined task completion","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Streamlined-task-completion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"People should be able to complete a task without distractions. Assistive Access reduces the available options, so people can find and navigate to their items of interest. Fewer steps and fewer options can help provide a clear path to success in completing a task.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Error prevention and recovery","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Error-prevention-and-recovery"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Recognizing and recovering from errors can be difficult. When people encounter significant actions, such as deleting a file, they should be given clear instructions and given the opportunity to understand what is happening before continuing. This also includes reducing actions that are time-dependent and make it easy to go back at any time.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Consistency","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Consistency"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Creating familiar interactions and patterns is crucial to Assistive Access. It establishes a sense of predictability and comfort, while also engaging in a multi-modal experience, like seeing both text and images. This helps reduce cognitive strain, makes the interface familiar, and increases the chance the interface will be understood.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Your app","level":1,"type":"heading","anchor":"Your-app"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When opening an app with Assistive Access a large ‚ÄúBack‚Äù button is added to the bottom of the screen. The button takes the user back to the Home screen.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app is displayed in a reduced frame by default."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC23-10032-app","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Optimized for Assistive Access","level":1,"type":"heading","anchor":"Optimized-for-Assistive-Access"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your app is adaptive to varying devices and screen sizes add the new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UISupportsFullScreenInAssistiveAccess"},{"type":"text","text":" key to your app‚Äôs "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Info.plist"},{"type":"text","text":" and set its value to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Yes"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Great apps on iPhone and iPad are designed to have a consistent layout that adapts regardless of your user‚Äôs device. This means that your app does not hard code layout based on the device or screen size.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC23-10032-app2"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"SwiftUI","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"SwiftUI"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In SwiftUI use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HStack"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VStack"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Grid"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GridRow"},{"type":"text","text":" views to arrange views, and the layout modifiers "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".alignmentGuide"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".safeAreaInset"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See more in the session:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc22\/10056","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"UIKit","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"UIKit"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In UIKit use AutoLayout and the ","type":"text"},{"code":"safeAreaInsets","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"safeAreaLayoutGuide","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" properties to position and adjust views.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See more in the session ‚ÄúUIKit: Apps for Every Size and Shape‚Äù from WWDC18."}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Resources","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Resources"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/forums\/tags\/wwdc2023-10032","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/forums\/create\/question?tag1=2&tag2=633030","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/bundleresources\/information_property_list\/uisupportsfullscreeninassistiveaccess","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Check out also","level":1,"type":"heading","anchor":"Check-out-also"},{"inlineContent":[{"overridingTitle":"Compose custom layouts with SwiftUI - WWDC22","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc22\/10056","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Compose custom layouts with SwiftUI - WWDC22"}],"isActive":true},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/devstreaming-cdn.apple.com\/videos\/wwdc\/2018\/235gkyrtsva0gy\/235\/235_uikit_apps_for_every_size_and_shape.pdf","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Written By","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Written-By"},{"numberOfColumns":